Cell["\<\
The scatterplot seems to suggest that it should be possible to predict, for \
example, a value of y for x = 3.5 which was not seen in the training dataset. \
One can do this by training a predictor (note the difference with the term \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]classifier\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] used in previous \
sections for classification models).\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8140883179335365`*^9, 
  3.814088436937512*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"45363dd5-f1d0-4dd4-98ed-\
d9ae7ea9712e"]
}, Open  ]],

