Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Tasks for you", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8143758920178857`*^9, 
  3.8143758969367313`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"848fe473-a7c8-493c-97ec-\
ceadaa57efdd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Task 1.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (Hard) Although it is not necessary to program methods from scratch (i.e. \
no need to reinvent the wheel), if interested, build a function to implement \
the regression tree method for generic 1-dimensional data from scratch."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814375903345625*^9, 3.8143759053621974`*^9}, {
  3.8143760667785225`*^9, 3.814376502045989*^9}, {3.8143768183769827`*^9, 
  3.814376826217019*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7c243774-73d6-4ffa-8b0c-\
491bcfa6e98a"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Example: Predicting the price of houses", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777465761739552*^9, 3.7774657851315536`*^9}, {
  3.780551268731629*^9, 3.7805512892673855`*^9}, {3.7805516488632665`*^9, 
  3.780551663032872*^9}, {3.813412864308385*^9, 3.8134128755642805`*^9}, {
  3.8141021479227524`*^9, 
  3.8141021489171286`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3767f141-4b2c-4a48-80f0-\
6e4ed34c318d"],

Cell["\<\
We will now look at a classical ML prediction example which trains a model to \
predict the price of houses based on 13 input variables for houses in a \
training set. The dataset is a bit old (from 1980) but it is a very useful \
example to illustrate prediction methods.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777466624042672*^9, 3.7774667203313437`*^9}, {
  3.7774668631631613`*^9, 3.777466864123397*^9}, {3.777466897547434*^9, 
  3.777466928459105*^9}, {3.7805511891963997`*^9, 
  3.7805512501345034`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"be53a88b-8394-4369-897c-\
90aca15313af"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The data", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7805480075321555`*^9, 
  3.7805480105250273`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9e388fcb-eb17-4988-b5d3-\
53c9dfb53437"],

