Cell[TextData[{
 "The predictor ",
 StyleBox["underestimates for low price and high price houses",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". \nIt does better for houses with intermediate prices."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777468237673761*^9, 3.7774682924096327`*^9}, {
   3.7801463966407747`*^9, 3.780146406298524*^9}, 3.780548639687976*^9, {
   3.7805506972382293`*^9, 
   3.780550700003319*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c5174ba5-3cf1-44f7-a11b-\
d08dde175d3e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ",
 StyleBox["residual plot",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " is another way to see the differences between predicted and actual values \
of instances. Specifically, the residual plot gives the difference \n\n\t\t\t\
\t\t\tResiduals = (actual value) - (predicted value)\n\nfor each instance. \
The residual plot for the test dataset looks as follows:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.77746819120961*^9, 3.7774682278499527`*^9}, {
  3.7805482150937543`*^9, 3.780548323659521*^9}, {3.780548365497821*^9, 
