Cell["\<\
On average, the actual value of houses is higher than the predicted value:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.780550180975024*^9, 
  3.78055022796984*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"418bddf3-1ca7-4ece-84c0-\
e2eacec4b611"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Mean", "[", "residuals", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7805501275668507`*^9, 3.780550141472892*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[24]:=",ExpressionUUID->"2f3fcf9c-1da3-4538-93ad-8e11f8f4e645"],

Cell[BoxData["0.1082647008463478`"], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.780550134699444*^9, 3.780550142034953*^9}, 
   3.7818666892513046`*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[24]=",ExpressionUUID->"9f3daa20-6691-4878-9c15-1a2700facf16"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
This suggests that, on average, the predictor underestimates the price. \
However, we have seen above that the situation is slightly more complicated \
since under-prediction applies to houses with low and high prices.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.780550232126277*^9, 3.7805503204550433`*^9}, {
  3.7805503861206427`*^9, 3.780550426157547*^9}, {3.7805513014691763`*^9, 
  3.780551307022155*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3ebe17bd-cc11-4677-9e4f-\
dc87f88be6a1"],

Cell["In fact, looking at the standard deviation,", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777468370569628*^9, 3.777468392665637*^9}, {
  3.780550431173339*^9, 
  3.7805504432524996`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"10f8f869-bb48-4636-9ae6-\
6d34e00d627e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"bhpm", "[", "\"\<StandardDeviation\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777468356314354*^9, 3.777468360714161*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[25]:=",ExpressionUUID->"512f4b0c-ef1f-4e73-9756-9bc5c4b86a73"],

Cell[BoxData["5.701297278001608`"], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.777468361398242*^9, 3.78186678644163*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[25]=",ExpressionUUID->"c7ffa65c-37dc-4531-ba64-01ecfda3287b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
which gives an idea of the typical error of the prediction, we would conclude \
that a mean value of 0.1 cannot be taken as a significant difference between \
predicted and actual values of houses. Indeed, the prediction error is \
significantly larger than the mean value.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7805504480413713`*^9, 
  3.7805505529649067`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"96dfa5d7-3910-4390-8652-\
43ea99c4217d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "It is also interesting to look at the ",
 StyleBox["distribution of the residuals.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "  \nIt can be visualized by plotting a histogram:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7805488445685883`*^9, 3.7805488737155495`*^9}, {
  3.780548967306411*^9, 3.780548981905756*^9}, {3.780550562244397*^9, 
  3.780550589715622*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"024cc53b-bc1f-4748-9f45-\
bffb7ebf55e7"],

